headline: EU new car registrations down 1.9% in November
summary: In November, new EU car registrations fell by 1.9%, the ACEA reports. France led the way with a sharp 12.7% decline, followed by Italy, down 10.8%, while the German market stagnated slightly. Among the four most significant EU markets, only Spain recorded positive growth of 6.4%, the group added. Publicly traded companies in the space include Ford (F), General Motors (GM), Honda (HMC), Mercedes-Benz (MBGYY), Nissan (NSANY), Stellantis (STLA), Tesla (TSLA), Toyota (TM) and Volkswagen (VWAGY).
